"title": "7967: spiritual gifts, and responsibility",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7967: spiritual gifts, and responsibility",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A spiritual gift may be intended to equip its recipient for a specific function or appointment. Those who are equipped in this way need the enabling power of God's spirit to carry out their appointed tasks.</p>\n<h2>OT examples of God's gifts or appointments</h2>\n<h3>God appoints prophets</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:5\">JER 1:5</a></strong></p>\n<h3>God appoints Israel's kings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:11\">1SA 15:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:8\">2SA 7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:7\">2SA 12:7</a></p>\n<h3>God appoints the Persian king Cyrus</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:1\">ISA 45:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:2\">ISA 41:2</a></p>\n<h3>God empowers leaders and kings with his Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:18\">NUM 27:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:10\">JDG 3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:34\">JDG 6:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:29\">JDG 11:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:25\">JDG 13:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:6\">JDG 14:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:19\">JDG 14:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:14\">JDG 15:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:6\">1SA 10:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:10\">1SA 10:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:6\">1SA 11:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:13-1Sam16:14\">1SA 16:13–16:14</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit is given to the servant of the LORD</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1\">ISA 42:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1\">ISA 61:1</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is endowed with the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:16-Matt3:17\">MAT 3:16–3:17</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:10-Mark1:11\">MRK 1:10–1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:21-Luke3:22\">LUK 3:21–3:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:32-John1:33\">JHN 1:32–1:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:38\">ACT 10:38</a></p>\n<h2>The apostles are endowed with the Holy Spirit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Spiritual gifts given to the church</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11\">EPH 4:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:28\">1CO 12:28</a></p>\n<h3>Many functions within the church yet unity is preserved</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:4-Eph4:7\">EPH 4:4–4:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:4-1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:4–12:11</a></p>\n<h3>All Christians are appointed to build up the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:15-Eph4:16\">EPH 4:15–4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:12\">1CO 12:12</a></p>\n<h2>The experience of spiritual gifts</h2>\n<h3>Associated with the laying on of hands</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:6-2Tim1:7\">2TI 1:6–1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:10\">NUM 8:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:18\">NUM 27:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:9\">DEU 34:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:6\">ACT 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:14\">1TI 4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:22\">1TI 5:22</a></p>\n<h3>Associated with prayer and fasting</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:23\">ACT 14:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:3\">ACT 13:3</a></p>\n<h2>Spiritual gifts must not to be neglected</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:14\">1TI 4:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:11-Luke19:26\">LUK 19:11–19:26</a></p>",
